options.content:
This dashboard requires ONTAP 9.8+ and the APIs are only available via REST. Two actions are required to use this dashboard:
1. On Harvest, enable the REST collector in your `harvest.yml` config
2. On your ONTAP cluster, enable File System Analytics (FSA) for one or more volumes. See https://docs.netapp.com/us-en/ontap/task_nas_file_system_analytics_enable.html for more details.

Note: Prior to version 9.13.1, ONTAP requires you to enable FSA individually for each volume. Harvest only collects FSA metrics from FSA-enabled volumes on the cluster. By default, Harvest keeps track of the 20 largest volumes for FSA. If you wish to customize this, please see: https://github.com/NetApp/harvest/blob/main/conf/rest/9.12.0/volume_analytics.yaml.

panels.description: The virtual space used (includes volume reserves) before storage efficiency, in bytes.
panels.title: Used

panels.description: Total size of AFS, excluding snap-reserve, in bytes.
panels.title: Size

panels.description: Total directory count including the root and children directories.
panels.title: Directories

panels.description: The actual number of bytes used on disk by this file. If byte_offset and length parameters are specified, this will return the bytes used by the file within the given range.
panels.title: Top $TopResources Volumes by Directory Growth

panels.description: Total number of files in root and child directories.
panels.title: Files

list.definition: query_result(volume_analytics_dir_bytes_used{datacenter=~"$Datacenter",netapp_cluster=~"$Cluster", svm=~"$SVM"} * on (datacenter, netapp_cluster, svm, volume) group_left(tags) volume_labels{netapp_cluster=~"$Cluster",datacenter=~"$Datacenter",svm=~"$SVM",tags=~".*$Tag.*"})
list.name: Volume
